Please answer the following multiple-choice question. You MUST start your answer with a single letter (A, B, C, or D).

Question: What was the most common method used by local officials to falsify data during the Great Leap Forward?

Options:
A. &quot;Exaggerated Report&quot;
B. &quot;Free food&quot;
C. &quot;Backward Method&quot;
D. Both A and B are correct
